      In the <a href=3D"https://www.gsn-lib.org/apps/raytracing/index.php" =
class=3D"externalLink">Vulkan GLSL Ray Tracing Emulator</a> this is achieve=
d
      with the following code:</p>
      <pre class=3D"myHackyShaderHighlight" style=3D"color:#000000;backgrou=
nd:#eee; margin-top:0px; font-size: 0.8em;"><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;=
">// gsnShaderOptions: precompiler=3D"GL_EXT_ray_tracing, recursion: 2, app=
: 1"
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// IMPORTANT: do not remove the lin=
e above
</span>
<span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">/**** ABOUT ****/</span>
<span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// A minimal example
</span>
<span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">/**** COMMON START ****/</span>
<span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// In the COMMON section, the structs "Ray=
PayloadType" and "HitAttributeType" must be defined.
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// Furthermore, your own helper fun=
ctions must be defined here (can be called in all shaders).
</span>
struct RayPayloadType {
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> color; <span style=3D"color:da=
rkgreen;">// unused
</span>}; <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// type of the "payload" variabl=
e
</span>
struct HitAttributeType {
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> normal; <span style=3D"color:d=
arkgreen;">// unused
</span>}; <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// type of the "hit" variable
</span>
<span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">/**** COMMON END ****/</span>

<span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// Ray tracing shaders must be defined in =
the following order:
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// ray generation, closest-hit, mis=
s, intersection, any-hit
</span>
<span style=3D"color:#930f80;">void</span> main() { <span style=3D"color:da=
rkgreen;">/**** RAY GENERATION SHADER ****/</span>
  <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// set RGBA color
</span>  gsnSetPixel(<span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec4</span>(<span style=
=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span>, <span style=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span>, <span =
style=3D"color:blue;">0.0</span>, <span style=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span>));
}
</pre>
      <p>All commented lines are not necessary, except for the first line, =
which invokes the pre-compiler.=20
        Consequently, if you like it as short as possible, this code works =
as well:
      </p>
      <pre class=3D"myHackyShaderHighlight" style=3D"color:#000000;backgrou=
nd:#eee; margin-top:0px; font-size: 0.8em;"><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;=
">// gsnShaderOptions: precompiler=3D"GL_EXT_ray_tracing, recursion: 2, app=
: 1"
</span>struct RayPayloadType {
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> color;
};

struct HitAttributeType {
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> normal;
};

<span style=3D"color:#930f80;">void</span> main() {
  gsnSetPixel(<span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec4</span>(<span style=3D"col=
or:blue;">1.0</span>, <span style=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span>, <span style=
=3D"color:blue;">0.0</span>, <span style=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span>));
}
</pre>     =20
