    <h4 id=3D"launchid" class=3D"largeTopMargin">Example 2: gl_LaunchID</h4=
> =20
    <p>
      Only two built-in variables are accessible in the ray generation shad=
er, namely=20
      <code><span class=3D"variable">uvec3</span> <span class=3D"builtIn">g=
l_LaunchIDEXT</span></code>
      and <code><span class=3D"variable">uvec3</span> <span class=3D"builtI=
n">gl_LaunchSizeEXT</span></code>.=20
      In the emulator, the x- and y-dimension of the <code><span class=3D"b=
uiltIn">gl_LaunchSizeEXT</span></code> variable correspond
      to the width and height of the output image and the z-dimension is al=
ways set to 1. The
      <code><span class=3D"builtIn">gl_LaunchSizeEXT</span></code> variable=
 can be changed in the <b>Edit Scene</b> section of the user interface.
    </p>
    <p>The ray generation shader's <code>main()</code> function is called (=
in parallel) for each pixel of the output image and
      the <code><span class=3D"builtIn">gl_LaunchIDEXT</span></code> variab=
le can be used to determine the position within the image.
    </p>
    <p>In the following example, the red and green channels of the output i=
mage are set dependent on the values in the=20
       <code><span class=3D"builtIn">gl_LaunchIDEXT</span></code> variable.=
</p>
       <pre class=3D"myHackyShaderHighlight" style=3D"color:#000000;backgro=
und:#eee; margin-top:0px; font-size: 0.8em;"><span style=3D"color:#930f80;"=
>void</span> main() { <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">/**** RAY GENERATION=
 SHADER ****/</span>
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec4</span> outputColor =3D <span style=3D=
"color:#930f80;">vec4</span>(<span style=3D"color:blue;">0.0</span>, <span =
style=3D"color:blue;">0.0</span>, <span style=3D"color:blue;">0.0</span>, <=
span style=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span>);
  outputColor.r =3D <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">float</span>(gl_LaunchID=
EXT.x) / <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">float</span>(gl_LaunchSizeEXT.x);
  outputColor.g =3D <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">float</span>(gl_LaunchID=
EXT.y) / <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">float</span>(gl_LaunchSizeEXT.y);
  gsnSetPixel(outputColor);
}
</pre>      =20
=20
