    <h4 class=3D"largeTopMargin">Example 6: Accessing the Vertex Data of a =
Triangle Mesh</h4>
     <p>
      When the <span class=3D"shaderName">closest-hit</span> shader is call=
ed, the built-in variables <code><span class=3D"builtIn">gl_InstanceID</spa=
n></code>,
      <code><span class=3D"builtIn">gl_ObjectToWorldEXT</span></code>, and =
<code><span class=3D"builtIn">gl_PrimitiveID</span></code>=20
      are set accordingly and allow to identify the BLAS instance, its tran=
sformation, and the primitive (i.e., in this case, the triangle) of the clo=
sest hit location.=20
    </p>
    <p>
      The emulator provides three functions that take the <code><span class=
=3D"builtIn">gl_InstanceID</span></code> and <code><span class=3D"builtIn">=
gl_PrimitiveID</span></code>
      variables as input parameters and return the local vertex positions, =
local normals, and texture coordinates for
      the three vertices of the triangle that was hit.
    </p>
    <p>Furthermore, the barycentric coordinates of the closest hit location=
 are computed by=20
      the built-in triangle intersection and are passed to the closest-hit =
shader via the=20
       <code><span class=3D"variable">vec2</span> baryCoord</code> variable=
.=20
       Using the barycentric coordinates, the
       interpolated vertex data for the hit location can be computed.
    </p>
<pre class=3D"myHackyShaderHighlight" style=3D"color:#000000;background:#ee=
e; margin-top:0px; font-size: 0.8em;">...

<span style=3D"color:#930f80;">void</span>  main() { <span style=3D"color:d=
arkgreen;">/**** CLOSEST-HIT SHADER ****/</span>
 =20
  <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// get mesh vertex data in object space
</span>  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> p0, p1, p2;
  gsnGetPositions(<span style=3D"color:#ff8c00;">gl_InstanceID</span>, <spa=
n style=3D"color:#ff8c00;">gl_PrimitiveID</span>, p0, p1, p2);
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> n0, n1, n2;
  gsnGetNormals(<span style=3D"color:#ff8c00;">gl_InstanceID</span>, <span =
style=3D"color:#ff8c00;">gl_PrimitiveID</span>, n0, n1, n2);
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec2</span> t0, t1, t2;
  gsnGetTexCoords(<span style=3D"color:#ff8c00;">gl_InstanceID</span>, <spa=
n style=3D"color:#ff8c00;">gl_PrimitiveID</span>, t0, t1, t2);

  <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// interpolate with barycentric coordina=
tes
</span>  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> barys =3D <span style=
=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span>(<span style=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span>f - b=
aryCoord.x - baryCoord.y, baryCoord.x, baryCoord.y);
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> localNormal =3D <span style=3D=
"color:#ff8c00;">normalize</span>(n0 * barys.x + n1 * barys.y + n2 * barys.=
z);
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> localPosition =3D p0 * barys.x=
 + p1 * barys.y + p2 * barys.z;
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec2</span> texCoords =3D t0 * barys.x + t=
1 * barys.y + t2 * barys.z;

  <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// transform to world space
</span>  mat3 normalMat;
  gsnGetNormal3x3Matrix(<span style=3D"color:#ff8c00;">gl_InstanceID</span>=
, normalMat);
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> normal =3D <span style=3D"colo=
r:#ff8c00;">normalize</span>(normalMat * localNormal);
