    <h4 id=3D"camorbit" class=3D"largeTopMargin">Example 7: Moving the Came=
ra</h4>
    <p>In this example, a new helper function is added to the COMMON sectio=
n that produces rays for a camera that is looking from an
     "eye" point to reference point (both in world space). Changing the cam=
era parameters over time generates a moving camera.
    </p>
<pre class=3D"myHackyShaderHighlight" style=3D"color:#000000;background:#ee=
e; margin-top:0px; font-size: 0.8em;"><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// R=
eturns a camera ray for a camera located at the=20
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// eye point and looking at a refer=
ence point. Furthermore,
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// the up vector of the camera coor=
dinate system is required.
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// (similar to the OpenGL gluLookAt=
 function)
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// "fieldOfViewY" must be given in =
degrees.
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// "point" must be in range [0.0, 1=
.0] to cover the complete image plane.
</span><span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">//
</span><span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> getCameraRayLookAt(<span =
style=3D"color:#930f80;">float</span> fieldOfViewY, <span style=3D"color:#9=
30f80;">float</span> aspectRatio,=20
                        <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> eye, <sp=
an style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> ref, <span style=3D"color:#930f80;"=
>vec3</span> up, <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec2</span> point)=20
{
  <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// compute focal length from given field=
-of-view
</span>  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">float</span> focalLength =3D <span =
style=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span> / tan(<span style=3D"color:blue;">0.5</spa=
n> * fieldOfViewY * <span style=3D"color:blue;">3.14159265359</span> / <spa=
n style=3D"color:blue;">180.0</span>);
  <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// compute position in the camera's imag=
e plane in range [-1.0, 1.0]
</span>  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec2</span> pos =3D <span style=3D"=
color:blue;">2.0</span> * (point - <span style=3D"color:blue;">0.5</span>);
  <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// compute ray in camera space
</span>  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> rayCam =3D <span style=
=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span>(pos.x * aspectRatio, pos.y, -focalLength);
 =20
  <span style=3D"color:darkgreen;">// compute camera axes in world space
</span>  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> camZ =3D <span style=3D=
"color:#ff8c00;">normalize</span>(eye - ref);
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> v =3D <span style=3D"color:#ff=
8c00;">normalize</span>(up);
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> camX =3D <span style=3D"color:=
#ff8c00;">cross</span>(v, camZ);
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> camY =3D <span style=3D"color:=
#ff8c00;">cross</span>(camZ, camX);
 =20
  <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> rayWorld =3D camX * rayCam.x +=
 camY * rayCam.y + camZ * rayCam.z;
  return <span style=3D"color:#ff8c00;">normalize</span>(rayWorld);
}
</pre> =20
