    <h4 id=3D"antialiasing" class=3D"largeTopMargin">Example 11: Distribute=
d Ray Tracing / Anti-Aliasing</h4>

    <p>To prevent aliasing due to undersampling, we can send multiple rays =
per pixel.
    The random position of the ray inside the pixel must be uniformly distr=
ibuted.=20
    To prevent repeated sampling at the same position, pseudo-random low di=
screpancy sequences (such as=20
    the <a href=3D"https://www.gsn-lib.org/apps/raytracing/index.php?name=
=3Dexample_halton" class=3D"externalLink">Halton</a> or=20
    <a href=3D"https://www.gsn-lib.org/apps/raytracing/index.php?name=3Dexa=
mple_hammersley" class=3D"externalLink">Hammersley</a>) are often used in p=
ractice.
    By averaging the contributions of the rays, the correct color value for=
 the pixel can be determined.</p>
    <p>
    If the previous average is saved in the previous image, the new average=
 can be calculated as follows:
    </p>
    <pre class=3D"myHackyShaderHighlight" style=3D"color:#000000;background=
:#eee; margin-top:0px; font-size: 0.8em;"><span style=3D"color:#930f80;">ve=
c4</span> previousAverage =3D gsnGetPreviousPixel();
<span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec3</span> newAverage =3D (previousAverage.=
rgb * <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">float</span>(frameID) + payload.color)=
 / <span style=3D"color:#930f80;">float</span>(frameID +<span style=3D"colo=
r:blue;"> 1</span>);
gsnSetPixel(<span style=3D"color:#930f80;">vec4</span>(newAverage, <span st=
yle=3D"color:blue;">1.0</span>));
</pre>
